         <abstract>
            <p>The diophantine equation $X_1 + \cdots + X_k = X_1 \cdots X_k$ has at least one solution in positive integers for $k \geqslant 2$. The set of integers $k$ for which this is the only solution are investigated; in particular, this set is conjectured to be a known finite sequence.</p>
